# Cursor — novelty-theory-lean (Lean 4)

Agents **must** read and follow:

1. **`QUEUE.md`** — agent execution contract + cross-epic queue (**every sustained-work session**).
2. **`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`** — methodology: specs vs `docs/`, epic queues, handoff, **§8 papers + external-facing code**; **§7.3** describes how *parent* repos submodule **this** library.
3. **`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`** — **Lean proof quality** (primary); **Python/Node** if scripts appear; **external-facing names**; **LaTeX**; optional NEMS pack in `NOTES/`.
4. **`docs/000_INDEX.md`** — current doc map; update when adding/removing `docs/*.md`.
5. **Active spec + epic** — under `specs/INCOMPLETE/IN-PROCESS/`; cite specs as `SPEC_NNN_XXX` (number + suffix).

**Non-negotiables (summary):**

- Normative specs **only** under `specs/` — never under `docs/`.
- Do not edit migrations that have already run; add new migrations instead.
- Fix root causes; do not mask errors to “make it pass.”
- New `TODO` in code → track in `docs/005_TODO_REGISTRY.md` when practical.
- Multi-agent branches: commit **only files you changed** when possible.
- **`.gitignore`:** follow **`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`** §7.1–§7.2 (do not blanket-ignore **`.pdf`**, **`.md`**, needed **JSON/resources**, **`.env`** per policy; ignore **build artifacts** and **logs**; **Git LFS** for large files — verify `git lfs`).
- **Queue execution:** Process **`QUEUE.md`** and epic queues by **doing the work**; prefer the **strongest** Lean proofs and **most robust** Python/Node per [`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](CODING_PROTOCOLS.md); continue until epics are **closed**; **STOP AND ASK** only when truly blocked ([`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §5.2).
- **Lean:** On every Lean pass, **audit** for **`sorry`/gaps**, **axioms**, **vacuous statements**, **weak lemmas**, **definition smuggling** ([`QUEUE.md`](QUEUE.md) contract + [`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](CODING_PROTOCOLS.md) proof quality). **Layout:** this repo **is** the library root; see **[`QUEUE.md`](QUEUE.md)** §9 ([`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §7.3 for parent/submodule pattern).
- **Code surface:** **Role-based** names for external audiences; **no self-talk / meta-talk** in comments; **never** refer to **advisor / user / owner / PI / any person** in code, identifiers, or comments ([`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](CODING_PROTOCOLS.md)).
- **LaTeX papers:** **References** (`.bib` if used or requested); **appendices** (theorem inventory + dependency map) for Lean papers; **no** internal `docs/` / `specs` / `QUEUE` pointers in prose; **no** citing internal specs/docs (**exception:** explicit public codebase doc URL); **prologue** like **`Representational_Incompleteness.tex`** ([`/Users/nova/representational-incompleteness/lean/paper/Representational_Incompleteness.tex`](/Users/nova/representational-incompleteness/lean/paper/Representational_Incompleteness.tex)) — [`NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md`](NOTES/PROJECT_SEED.md) §8.

Project stack and commands: **[`CODING_PROTOCOLS.md`](CODING_PROTOCOLS.md)** (*Project specifics* — novelty-theory-lean) and **[`docs/002_DEVELOPER_SETUP.md`](docs/002_DEVELOPER_SETUP.md)**.
